The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Tuesday, June 15, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Tuesday, June 15, 2004				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	The Esplanade area in the afternoon. A Trinamul Youth Congress rally to protest starvation deaths in Amlashol will start from Victoria House at 2 pm and move along Bentinck Street, Free School Street, Chowringhee Road and Lindsay Street, ending at the Food Corporation of India office.				 																Talk				 																																	Madhusudan Bhattacharya, former professor of Jadavpur University, will speak on Revitalisation of the angel atop Victoria Memorial: theory of upkeep, on the Memorial premises, at 6 pm.				 																																	Rita Bhimani will speak on Corporate communications  the new human face as part of The CMA-Patton Tuesday Talkshoppe at CMA Auditorium, at 5.45 pm.				 																Export meet				 																																	The second edition of export summit, organised by Confederation of Indian Industry, in association with the state government, at Taj Bengal, 10 am.				 																Felicitation				 																																	Lok Sabha Speaker Somnath Chatterjee will be felicitated by Federation of Indian Chambers of Commerce and Industry at Oberoi Grand, at 3 pm.				 																On camera				 																																	A photography exhibition on Soumitra Chatterjee by Pratap K. Dasgupta will be inaugurated at Gaganendra Silpa Pradarshasala, at 7 pm.				 																Art beat				 																																	An all-India exhibition of paintings and sculptures on display at CIMA Gallery, 2 pm to 7 pm.
